"StrictHostKeyChecking" is a parameter in the "Host" section of the SSH config file.

It has three possible values:

"yes" means to always check the host keys.
"no" means to never check the host keys.
"ask" means to ask the user about the host keys.

The default value is "ask".

If you set it to "no", you won't be prompted to add new hosts to the known_hosts file.

